				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tradeskilling did not advance in GoD. 
<br />

<br />
There are no "nice" things to make with the new drops (at least that I have seen). No sweet armor pieces, no items with either great stats or effects.
<br />

<br />
About the only thing of interest are the Inferno Torches, which the in-guild smith is probably going to make using guild funds anyways.
<br />

<br />
There is no follow-on to Aid Grimel, which is pretty much just a trophy by the time you gain elemental access and finally collect all the crap and succeed in the combines. You're probably in Time, or close to it once you do.
<br />

<br />
Let's be real -- you don't need Preservation of Xegony with elemental sleeves (or any of the other pieces with PoX or better focii on them), and FT is a dime-a-dozen for elemental players. Other than a sense of accomplishment, why bother with
